Generate the temporal variation of population abundance with discret population growth and carrying capacity

Romain Lorrilliere

2023-04-07

Several model

Logistic

logistic equation

## function (N, r, K) 
## return(N + (r * N * (1 - N/K)))

Ricker (1968)

logistic equation

r is interpreted as an intrinsic growth rate and k as the carrying capacity

## function (N, r, K) 
## return(N * exp(r * (1 - N/K)))

Beverton Holt (1993)

logistic equation

Here R is interpreted as the proliferation rate per generation

## function (N, r, K) 
## return((r * N)/(1 + (N * (r - 1)/K)))

Without demographic stochasticity

With demographic stochasticity

Conclusion : Because of the strong temporal insatability of the Ricker model we will not use this model. For the futur simulation we will choose the Beverton-Holt.

Demographic stochasticity or not ?

Here I test the effect on the simulated dynamic to add a stochastic process according to a Poisson distribution or a predicted abundance rounded or keeping the predicted abundances (as a float number).
